# Copy this file to .env (or .env.local) and fill in the values.
# Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_ to the browser.

# ── Vehicle location map — Amazon Location Service Maps (optional) ─────────
# Renders the vehicle location map (MapLibre GL) inside vehicle group chats.
# All three are required to enable the map; if any is missing the map UI shows a
# themed "not configured" state and the rest of the app is unaffected.
#
#   VITE_AWS_LOCATION_API_KEY   the Amazon Location API key VALUE (looks like
#                               "v1.public.xxxxx") — NOT the key ARN. This is a
#                               READ-ONLY Maps key; tracker reads happen on the
#                               server with separate IAM credentials.
#   VITE_AWS_LOCATION_REGION    the key's region, e.g. eu-central-1
#   VITE_AWS_LOCATION_MAP_STYLE a v2 GeoMaps style name:
#                               Standard | Monochrome | Hybrid | Satellite
#                               (Standard or Monochrome pair best with the dark
#                               theme; color-scheme=Dark is applied automatically)
#
# Two Maps APIs are supported — set ONE of the style vars below:
#   • v2 GeoMaps key (actions GetTile/GetStaticMap): set VITE_AWS_LOCATION_MAP_STYLE
#       URL: https://maps.geo.${region}.amazonaws.com/v2/styles/${style}/descriptor?key=…&color-scheme=Dark
#   • legacy v1 Maps key (actions GetMap*): set VITE_AWS_LOCATION_MAP_NAME to a
#     Map resource you created in Amazon Location (a dark style like
#     VectorEsriDarkGrayCanvas matches the theme). Takes precedence if both set.
#       URL: https://maps.geo.${region}.amazonaws.com/maps/v0/maps/${name}/style-descriptor?key=…
VITE_AWS_LOCATION_API_KEY=
VITE_AWS_LOCATION_REGION=eu-central-1
VITE_AWS_LOCATION_MAP_STYLE=Standard
# VITE_AWS_LOCATION_MAP_NAME=

# ── Truck restrictions map style (optional) ───────────────────────────────
# The "Truck" map mode in Check route shows the HERE truck-restrictions style
# ("VectorHereExploreTruck" / "HERE Explore Truck") — truck width/height/weight
# limits and HAZMAT. v2 GeoMaps has NO truck style, so this is only available as
# a LEGACY v1 Map RESOURCE: in Amazon Location, create a Map with the
# "VectorHereExploreTruck" style and put its resource NAME here.
#   VITE_AWS_LOCATION_MAP_TRUCK_NAME  the truck Map resource name you created.
#   VITE_AWS_LOCATION_TRUCK_API_KEY   (optional) a geo:GetMap* key for that
#                                     resource, if different from the v2 key
#                                     above; otherwise the main key is reused.
# When unset, the Truck mode shows a themed "not available" message and Dark /
# Light keep working unchanged.
# VITE_AWS_LOCATION_MAP_TRUCK_NAME=VectorHereExploreTruck
# VITE_AWS_LOCATION_TRUCK_API_KEY=
